      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      664.05,
      557.88,
      677.33
    ],
    "text": "grappling with the woman on the day of the incident. But his son in his evidence said that the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      691.67,
      557.94,
      704.95
    ],
    "text": "Accused-Appellant in Court is not the person who ran away from the scene of offence. Thus in",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      721.79,
      312.05,
      735.07
    ],
    "text": "4",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      56.75,
      558.03,
      70.03
    ],
    "text": "our view the evidence of the son of Yesurasan creates a reasonable doubt in the evidence of",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      84.37,
      557.98,
      97.65
    ],
    "text": "Yesudasan .If the evidence of Tiron Ranjith who is the son of Yesudasan is accepted, the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      111.97,
      558.33,
      125.25
    ],
    "text": "Accused-Appellant will have to be acquitted. As I pointed out earlier, the evidence of Tiron",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      139.57,
      432.19,
      152.85
    ],
    "text": "Ranjith has created a reasonable doubt in the evidence of Yesurasan.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      194.77,
      558.04,
      208.05
    ],
    "text": "The Accused gave evidence under oath. The learned trial Judge after considering the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      222.37,
      558.34,
      235.65
    ],
    "text": "evidence of the Accused-Appellant did not either accept or reject the evidence of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      250.0,
      558.18,
      263.28
    ],
    "text": "Accused-Appellant. In a criminal trial when the Accused-Appellant gives evidence it is the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      277.6,
      558.02,
      290.88
    ],
    "text": "bounden duty of the trial Judge to consider the Accused\u2019s evidence and come to a conclusion",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      305.2,
      558.2,
      318.48
    ],
    "text": "whether he accepts or rejects the evidence of the Accused- Appellant or whether the evidence of",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      332.8,
      557.96,
      346.08
    ],
    "text": "the Accused-Appellant creates a reasonable doubt in the prosecution case. . If the learned Trial",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      360.4,
      558.21,
      373.68
    ],
    "text": "Judge fails to reject or accept the evidence of the Accused-Appellant, the question must be",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      388.02,
      558.06,
      401.3
    ],
    "text": "considered whether he is entitled to be acquitted. In this connection I would like to consider a",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      415.62,
      558.17,
      428.9
    ],
    "text": "judicial decision of the Court of Criminal Appeal Ariyadasa Vs Queen ( 68 NLR page",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      443.22,
      557.97,
      456.5
    ],
    "text": "66 ) His Lordship Justice T.S.Fernando, held as follows: \u201c The Accused is entitled to be",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      470.82,
      561.22,
      484.1
    ],
    "text": "acquitted even if his evidence though not believed , is such that it causes a jury to entertain a",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      498.42,
      288.41,
      511.7
    ],
    "text": "reasonable doubt in regard to his guilt \u201d.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      553.65,
      558.23,
      566.93
    ],
    "text": "In Martin Singho Vs Queen (69 CLW page 21 at page 22) His Lordship Justice T.S.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      581.25,
      558.09,
      594.53
    ],
    "text": "Fernando made the following observations. \u201cAs this Court has pointed out on many occasions",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      608.85,
      557.95,
      622.13
    ],
    "text": "in the past where an Accused person is not relying on a general or special exception contained",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      636.45,
      557.83,
      649.73
    ],
    "text": "in the Penal Code there is no burden on him to establish any fact. In this case the Appellant",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      664.05,
      540.32,
      677.33
    ],
    "text": "was not relying on any such exception. Even if the jury declined to believe the Appellant\u2019s",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      691.67,
      560.9,
      704.95
    ],
    "text": "version, he was yet entitled to be acquitted on the charge if his version raised in the mind of",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      721.79,
      312.05,
      735.07
    ],
    "text": "5",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      56.75,
      435.91,
      70.03
    ],
    "text": "the jury a reasonable doubt as to the truth of the prosecution version.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      56.64,
      111.97,
      558.19,
      125.25
    ],
    "text": "In Queen Vs Kularatne ( 71 NLR page 529) considering the question as how to",
